  "prompt": "Which organ is supplied with most blood.?",
  "response": "The organ supplied with the most blood in the human body is the **liver**. The liver receives approximately 25% of the total cardiac output, which is about 1,500 milliliters of blood per minute. This is due to its critical roles in metabolism, detoxification, and nutrient processing.\n\nThe liver has a dual blood supply:\n1. **Hepatic artery** (supplies oxygen-rich blood).\n2. **Portal vein** (supplies nutrient-rich blood from the digestive tract).\n\nOther highly vascularized organs include the **kidneys** (which receive about 20% of cardiac output for filtration) and the **brain** (which receives about 15% of cardiac output). However, the liver surpasses these in terms of total blood flow.",
